# QA Report Format (iO)

Use this structure whenever you produce QA artifacts for iO (report, fix list, Confluence page, Jira tickets).

## Severity levels

| Level | Label | When to use |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| **Critical** | `P0` / Critical | Blocking: security, data loss, broken main flow, legal/a11y blocker |
| **High** | `P1` / High | Major: wrong behaviour, broken subflow, serious UX or API contract break |
| **Medium** | `P2` / Medium | Notable: inconsistency, missing edge handling, minor UX/API issue |
| **Low** | `P3` / Low | Nice-to-fix: polish, minor copy, small improvement |

## Single finding format

For each finding use:

- **ID:** Short unique id (e.g. `FE-01`, `API-02`, `E2E-03`).
- **Title:** One line, imperative (e.g. "Fix login button disabled state on error").
- **Area:** One of `Frontend` | `Backend` | `E2E` | `API` | `Security` | `Other`.
- **Severity:** P0–P3 (or Critical/High/Medium/Low).
- **Steps:** How to reproduce (numbered list or "N/A" for code-level only).
- **Expected vs actual:** One line each.
- **Suggestion:** What to change (file/component/endpoint + concrete fix).
- **Evidence:** Link to video, screenshot path, or "See recording: …".

## QA Report (main artifact)

Structure:

```markdown
# QA Report — [Project name] — [Date/branch]

## Summary
- Total findings: N (P0: x, P1: x, P2: x, P3: x)
- Areas: Frontend, Backend, E2E (as applicable)

## Findings

### [Area] — [Finding title] [Px]
- **ID:** …
- **Steps:** …
- **Expected / Actual:** …
- **Suggestion:** …
- **Evidence:** …

(Repeat per finding.)

## Videos / recordings
- [Title]: path or URL
```

## Fix list (for PM → Jira)

Table format (PM can copy into Jira or you create tickets via MCP):

| ID | Title | Severity | Area | Suggested ticket summary |
|----|--------|----------|------|--------------------------|
| FE-01 | Fix login button disabled state | P1 | Frontend | Login button stays disabled after API error; re-enable and show message |
| … | … | … | … | … |

- One row per finding.
- "Suggested ticket summary" = one line for Jira title or description.

## Confluence QA checklist

- Same findings as the report, rendered as a checklist page:
  - **QA Run:** [project] — [date]
  - **Scope:** Frontend / Backend / E2E (what was run)
  - For each finding: `- [ ] [ID] [Title] (Px) — [one-line suggestion]`
  - Section for "Videos / demos" with links.

## Jira tickets (when creating via MCP)

- **Summary:** Use "Suggested ticket summary" from fix list (or the finding title).
- **Description:** Include steps, expected/actual, suggestion, link to video if any.
- **Labels/components:** Use project conventions; add e.g. `qa`, `qa-2026-03` if agreed.
- **Issue type:** Bug or Task as per project.

Keep wording clear and actionable so PM and devs can use it without extra explanation.
